sentences.text:
I am satisfied that I should make an order to the effect that, subject to the Commissioner providing an indemnity to the liquidator and to PAAN in respect of costs to be incurred by PAAN or which it may be ordered to pay in the proposed proceedings and providing security in respect of that indemnity, the terms of such indemnity and the nature and amount of such security to be agreed between the Commissioner, the liquidator and PAAN or, failing agreement, settled by the registrar: 
(a) the Commissioner be authorised at his own expense and risk as to costs, to use the name of PAAN as a plaintiff or co-plaintiff in the proposed proceedings;

(b) the Commissioner indemnify the liquidator for all costs reasonably incurred by PAAN in respect of the proposed proceedings.
